Vengeance bites back in heart-pounding thriller ‘Muzzle’. Streaming on @primevideouk November 14. 

Synopsis: This crime thriller has just as much bite as it does bark. LAPD K-9 officer Jake Rosser (Aaron Eckhart, The Dark Knight) and his K-9 partner battle it out on the streets of LA when they get into a shootout with local drug dealers.
Blocked by Internal Affairs, muzzled by his own superiors from finding the shooter’s identity, Jake resolves to go rogue and partners with “Socks”, a violent K-9 with titanium incisors and a mysterious past. Jake and Socks aim to uncover a vast conspiracy that has a chokehold on the city and take vengeance on those responsible. Also starring Stephen Lang (Avatar: The Way of Water), Nick Searcy (Justified), Penelope Mitchell (Star Trek: Picard) and Diego Tinoco (On My Block), Muzzle is directed by John Stalberg Jr. (Crypto) and written by Stalberg Jr. and Carlyle Eubank (The Signal).
